OASISFormat: 0.3
Name: vg
Version: 0.0.1
Synopsis: Declarative 2D vector graphics for OCaml
Authors: Daniel Bünzli <daniel.buenzli at erratique.ch>
Copyrights: (c) 2013 Daniel C. Bünzli
License: BSD3
Homepage: http://erratique.ch/software/vg
Description:
 Vg is a module for declarative 2D vector graphics. Renderers for
 PDF, SVG and the HTML canvas element are bundled with the library 
 and an API allows to implement new renderers.
 .
 Vg depends on [Gg][1] and, optionally, on [js_of_ocaml][2] 
 for the HTML canvas element renderer. 
 .
 Vg is distributed under the BSD3 license.
 .
 [1]: http://erratique.ch/software/gg
 [2]: http://ocsigen.org/js_of_ocaml/

